The United States Army has reportedly approved hormone therapy that will allow imprisoned national secrets leaker Chelsea Manning to transition to a woman.

Manning, 27, is serving a 35-year sentence at Fort Leavenworth prison in Kansas after being convicted of giving thousands of classified documents to WikiLeaks while working as an Army intelligence analyst.

She was known by the name Bradley at the time. 

