The Army's approval of Manning's transition was first reported by USA TODAY.

In an Army memo, the commandant of Fort Leavenworth's Disciplinary Barracks, Col. Erica Nelson, wrote: 'After carefully considering the recommendation that (hormone treatment) is medically appropriate and necessary, and weighing all associated safety and security risks presented, I approve adding (hormone treatment) to Inmate Manning's treatment plan.'

