The military does not allow transgender individuals to serve although the Department of Veterans Affairs does provide hormone therapy treatment for veterans.

Air Force Secretary Deborah Lee James previously told USA TODAY the transgender troops ban should be lifted. 

There were 3,177 veterans diagnosed with gender identity disorder from 2001 to 2011,, according to the department of Veterans Affairs. 

It's not clear when Manning's treatment will begin. 

